    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-29T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="516"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d516">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">339.115 General Motors Export Co./184:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-29T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >May 29, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. My despatches number 2483 and number 2510, May 10 and 18.<note n="31"
                        xml:id="d516fn31">Despatch No. 2510, May 18, not printed.</note> Court of
                    Appeals today reversed decision of lower court which imposed fine of $2,000 on
                    Dominican Tobacco Company, condemned company to penalty of 2 years imprisonment
                    in the person of its president and to pay costs of proceeding.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
